race.comment: TWINKLE VAN WINKLE (12) came home strongly last start to finish third, beaten a long neck, over 1400m at Bendigo when resuming after a spell. Will be tough to stop again. SHE FLYS (13) ran a much-improved race last start, when beaten only 2.75 lengths at Bendigo, and only needs to run up to that to be in the firing line here. THE RIGHT PAGE (5) did a great job in the debut prep with a win and a couple of placings from just four starts and you'd think she's got to be a better horse this time around. AHAB (1) doesn't boast a great winning strike rate, but is a consistent type and it'd be a shock if he wasn't around the mark again despite the big weight.
